name: thedailybeast
text: Perdue acquired up to $190,000 in BWX Technologies stock. The firm had lucrative contracts with the Navy to develop high-tech components for its nuclear submarine fleet—and they were looking to expand with the 2019 National Defense Authorization Act. https://t.co/pqIrXrJxIb

name: thedailybeast
text:
Perdue had a key role in shaping the final version of the NDAA, including securing a hefty $4.7 billion for Virginia-class submarines.

Now guess which firm was awarded contracts to design and make key parts for Virginia-class submarines? BWX.
https://t.co/pqIrXrJxIb

name: thedailybeast
text: From February to July, as he was shaping the defense bill, Perdue reported selling off all his shares of BWX. The senator’s final financial disclosure form reported earnings of $15,000 to $50,000. https://t.co/pqIrXrrWjB

name: thedailybeast
text: “Members have inside information about our national security and defense spending, and personally benefiting from that information should be banned,” said Scott Amey, the general counsel of the Project on Government Oversight. https://t.co/pqIrXrJxIb
